@description.name: @description
@description.body: GeoPosition event used by GeoLocation class.

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Create a new instance.

@description.name: @description
@description.body: The time when the position was acquired.

@description.name: @description
@description.body: The angular distance north or south of the earth's equator, measured in decimal degrees along a meridian

@description.name: @description
@description.body: The angular distance on the earth's surface, measured east or west from the prime meridian at Greenwich, England, in decimal degrees

@description.name: @description
@description.body: The height of the position, specified in meters above the earth's surface.

@description.name: @description
@description.body: The accuracy level of the latitude and longitude coordinates specified in meters.

@description.name: @description
@description.body: The accuracy level of the altitude specified in meters.

@description.name: @description
@description.body: The direction of travel of the hosting device specified in degrees in a range from 0 to 360, counting clockwise relative to the true north. If the implementation cannot provide heading information, the value of this attribute must be null. If the hosting device is stationary (i.e. the value of the speed attribute is 0), then the value of the heading property must be NaN.

@description.name: @description
@description.body: The current ground speed of the hosting device specified in meters per second. If the implementation cannot provide speed information, the value of this property must be null.

@description.name: @description
@description.body: The owning object

@description.name: @description
@description.body: {String} The ID of the object.

@description.body: Initialize the fields of the event.
